{"id":"food-kkakdugi-049","q":"What is kkakdugi, the Korean kimchi variation made from cubed radish?","a":"Korean kimchi variation made from cubed radish (daikon)","d":["Korean kimchi made from whole cabbage leaves","Korean kimchi made from sliced cucumber","Korean kimchi made from water kimchi broth","Korean kimchi made from green onion","Korean kimchi made from perilla leaves","Korean kimchi made from mustard greens"],"e":"Kkakdugi is a variety of kimchi made from cubed Korean radish (mu), seasoned with gochugaru, garlic, ginger, and fish sauce, then fermented. The radish maintains its crunch, giving kkakdugi a different texture from baechu kimchi (cabbage kimchi). It is commonly served alongside beef bone soup (seolleongtang).","l1":null,"l2":null,"i":{"fixed":["q","a","e","distractors"]}}
