{"id":"food-olluquito-106","q":"What Andean dried meat (charqui) is traditionally used in the Peruvian stew olluquito?","a":"Charqui (dried and salted llama or beef)","d":["Alpaca jerky","Guinea pig dried meat","Guanaco cured meat","Vicuña dried meat","Dried rabbit","Smoked deer"],"e":"Olluquito con charqui combines thinly sliced olluco (a colorful Andean tuber) with rehydrated charqui. Charqui is meat — traditionally llama or beef — dried and salted at high altitude in a pre-Incan preservation method. The dish predates the Inca Empire. Note: the Quechua word 'charqui' is the origin of the English word 'jerky.'","l1":null,"l2":null,"i":{"fixed":["q","a","e","distractors"]}}
