{"id":"food-pemmican-017","q":"What is pemmican, the traditional Indigenous North American concentrated food made from rendered fat and dried meat?","a":"concentrated mixture of rendered tallow, dried meat, and dried berries","d":["smoked fish preserved in salt brine","dried corn ground into portable meal","jerky strips seasoned with berry sauce","animal blood mixed with grains and fat","fruit leather combined with meat paste","grain cakes mixed with animal grease"],"e":"Pemmican is a highly caloric, shelf-stable food originally made by various Indigenous peoples of North America. Dried lean meat (usually bison or deer) was pounded fine and mixed with rendered fat (tallow) and sometimes dried berries. It kept for years and became vital to fur traders and Arctic explorers.","l1":null,"l2":null,"i":{"fixed":["q","a","e","distractors"]}}
{"id":"food-pepernoot-053","q":"What is a pepernoot, the tiny Dutch spiced cookie associated with Sinterklaas celebrations?","a":"tiny Dutch spiced cookie made with cinnamon, anise, and ginger","d":["Belgian speculaas large windmill cookie","German Lebkuchen gingerbread cookie","Austrian Pfeffernüsse anise cookie","Danish pebernødder spiced nut cookie","Swedish pepparkakor thin ginger snap","French pain d'épices spice loaf"],"e":"Pepernoten are small, round, hard Dutch spiced cookies about the size of a marble, eaten during the Sinterklaas season. They are made with flour, syrup, butter, and spices including cinnamon, anise, nutmeg, and cloves. They differ from the larger, softer kruidnoten often confused with them.","l1":null,"l2":null,"i":{"fixed":["q","a","e","distractors"]}}
